    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="644"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d644">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/15268</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Lithuanian Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Zadeikis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-18">September 18,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of September 3, 1941<note n="14" xml:id="d644fn14">Not printed.</note>
                    protesting against the invasion of Lithuania by Germany and declaring that any
                    attempt on the part of Germany to shape the political future of Lithuania
                    without regard to the free will of the Lithuanian people and that any acts of
                    the German regime of occupation incompatible with the spirit of international
                    law will be considered void of any legality.<note n="15" xml:id="d644fn15"
                        >Similar notes had been received from the Latvian Minister on August 14,
                        1941, and from the Estonian representative on September 4, 1941.</note>
                </p>
                <p>You will recall that in the joint declaration agreed upon by the President of the
                    United States and the Prime Minister of Great Britain during their historic
                    meeting at sea<note n="16" xml:id="d644fn16">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_367">p. 367</ref>.</note> it
                    is stated that the United States and Great Britain respect the right of all
                    peoples to choose the form of Government under which they desire to live and
                    that the United States and Great Britain wish to see self-government restored to
                    those peoples who have been forcibly deprived of it.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>A. A. <hi rend="smallcaps">Berle, Jr</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
